  "body": "#In the latest version of react-native there is a warning in Status regarding setTimeout:\r\n\r\n> Setting a timer for a long period of time, i.e. multiple minutes, is a performance and correctness issue on Android as it keeps the timer module awake, amd timers can only be called when the app is in the foreground. See https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/12981 for more info.\r\n> (Saw setTimeout with duration 180000ms)\r\n\r\nAs far as I know this only concerns this line of code:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/edd4df85f95b42a459b9b189918c3b3f76102e3f/src/status_im/ui/screens/discover/events.cljs#L80-L82\r\n\r\n\r\n`dispatch-later` is not a viable alternative because it uses setTimeout internally as well.",
